Trying to find myself in the ECO community as a content creator, I had a chance to participate in a few content bounty votings. And here are my "insider" thoughts and visions about the current voting system I kept in my head for a long time.
For me there are 2 stages of content bounties:
1) First one (the one I really like and that gives me true joy and ability to realize myself in the creative way) - content creation stage.
2) Second one - voting process.
What about the second one?
Since early bounties we have had issues with it's honesty. This is the typical issue with online votings in such communities: nobody is protected from abuse. And this issue exists in Eco community and interferes with the objective points distribution. Voter role system was meant to reduce the percentage of abuse or resolve this issue completely, but it doesn't work now: users without voter status can vote freely (even those, who just came to the Eco Discord). It highly affected a lot of previous votings.
Why am i writing about it? I don't want to start a witch hunt or just complain about something, no. I do it to suggest ways to solve the issue - to provide a positive experience for future participants in the future bounty votings.

We have few ways to solve this issue:
1. Fix the Voter system: obvious idea, but i don't know the reason for this system shutdown. For my opinion: it provided a good cost-beneficial ratio, and for the first time it seemed like it solved the issue. But it has its cons: it required manual control (which is not so comfy for voter role "administrators"), had subjective issues and could be abused in some instances.
2. Improve the voter system to automate the voter role assignment: it seems possible to delegate this function to bot (it can check and sort members by a few threshold parameters: certain number of points, certain amount of time since the date of joining Eco channel, and a certain number of messages in the Eco channel). There is no need of manual control and no subjective issues, and it can significantly reduce the number of abusing cases (since there is still the possibility of abusing, abusing effect could be significantly reduced). But this requires hard technical work. If @Modestolich can comment on my words, I will be thankful!
3. Simpler way - to use #obshagfund experience: small cohort of trusted voters (it could be team members, overseas envoys or/and the most active members of the community [eg, unsung heroes or top points holders]) can hold a closed voting, provide to the public only the final result. This is a simple method and completely excludes the possibility of abuse. The main cons: subjectivity issues and closed nature of voting.

It works fine for me to use any of these methods, maybe someone has some thoughts about it too? It could be discussed here again. I really want to modernize the current voting system, so I'm ready to help if needed. 

Since the "quality over quantity" is what we strive for, we should care about it in the voting process too: votes quality over the votes quantity.

Hm, great input from you @one2fckU. 

So you are essentially proposing to do POP (proof of points) in the first case and closed voting of a small cohort of users in the second one. Choosing between these two I'll prefer the proof of points thing. It will involve a much larger group and will provide at least some transparency.

From my side, I can assure you that it is possible to do and it could be done relatively easily. We could even go further, we could create a "delegate option". For example, I'll be able to vote but (let's imagine) don't have time for that and I trust you to make decisions on my behalf. So I "transfer my voting power to you" via discord message.

Also, (I'm not sure here 100%) but we can create a trust chain. For example, If I was talking on some channels and tagged you - this will probably mean that you participated in some kind of interesting discussion. In other words, we could check whether the users have been tagged by `voters` enough times and assign them a voter role. (But this system need polishing because there are obvious ways to game the system).
